The SQL query that counts the number of occurrences for each value of the field order_type in the table orders is:

SELECT order_type, COUNT(*) FROM orders GROUP BY order_type;

This query uses the GROUP BY clause to group the records in the orders table based on the values in the order_type field, and the COUNT(*) function to count the number of occurrences of each value in each group. The result of this query will be a table with one row for each unique value in the order_type field, showing the value and the number of occurrences of that value in the orders table.
